  <artifactId>workshop-installer</artifactId>
  <packaging>pom</packaging>
  <name>Workshop Installer — Native Executable Packaging</name>
  <description>
    Produces native installers via jpackage:
      Windows: ClaudeArchitectWorkshop.exe (bundles JRE — no Java needed on target machine)
      Linux:   claude-architect-workshop.deb / .rpm

    Users configure Claude Desktop / Cursor to point to the .exe directly.
    They never need to know Java is involved.

    PLACEHOLDER: jpackage configuration will be added in Phase 4.
    This module exists now so the multi-module structure is complete.
  </description>

  <!--
    CERTIFICATION NOTE — Claude Code Configuration & Workflows (20% of exam)
    The installer output is what gets registered in Claude Desktop's
    mcpServers configuration. The path in claude_desktop_config.json
    points to the .exe produced here. Understanding how MCP servers
    are discovered and launched is part of the Tool Design domain.

    Example claude_desktop_config.json entry (produced in Phase 4):
    The "command" points to the .exe and "args" passes the API key flag.
    Full JSON example is in the project README (Phase 4).
  -->

  <!--
    No Java sources in this module.
    jpackage reads the fat JAR from workshop-server/target/ and wraps it.
    Full jpackage plugin configuration: Phase 4.
  -->

</project>
